    "description": "If you're a passionate Credit Analyst with drive and ambition, EY India Asia Pacific Associates in Aurangabad is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout EY India Asia Pacific Associates:\nEY India Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in GST\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Learning & development budget\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with EY India Asia Pacific Associates!",
